  "elapsed_s": 5.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I think the tribunal, if I can just guess and what others have guessed as well, I think they felt that, although he was certainly a very powerful man from 1942 on in connection with the enslavement of people and the treatment of prisoners of war and so forth, I think the tribunal felt that this willingness to admit some collective guilt was a reason for mitigating his-- what they might have sentenced him to.",
      "word_count": 76
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They sentenced Sauckel, who had really-- almost the subordinate to Speer, in the sense that, when Speer said, I need so many hundred thousand laborers, Sauckel went out and grabbed them and brought them in from other countries and so forth.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Sauckel was sentenced to death, but Speer got 20 years.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "The only reason I can see that being is that Speer became more contrite and more willing to disclose what had happened.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, he was, first, Hitler's architect.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And of course, that had nothing to do with the trial.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But during the war, after a man by the name of Fritz Todt, T-O-D-T, who was head of the Todt Organization-- and that was an organization that took skilled laborers and unskilled, but became very much a tool of the Nazi regime to build factories, to rebuild underground places of work, and so on, after the bombings got going, and so forth.",
      "word_count": 62
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "When-- when Fritz Todt died in an airplane accident, Hitler immediately put Speer in to succeed him.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he was made Reich Minister of War Production.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "24 were indicted.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "One committed suicide, but that was what I call my first defendant, Robert Ley, L-E-Y.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
